1️⃣ Concept Teaching (Strict, Clear, GATE-Oriented)
🔹 What is Pipelining?

Pipelining is a technique where:

👉 Multiple instructions are executed overlappingly
👉 Different stages work simultaneously

📌 Like an assembly line.

🔹 Basic Idea

Without pipelining:

One instruction completes fully before next starts

With pipelining:

Next instruction starts before previous finishes
🔹 Pipeline Stages (5-stage model)

1️⃣ IF – Instruction Fetch
2️⃣ ID – Instruction Decode
3️⃣ EX – Execute
4️⃣ MEM – Memory Access
5️⃣ WB – Write Back

🔹 Pipeline Diagram Concept

At each clock cycle:

Different instructions are in different stages
